# User-local configuration. Copy audit.conf.example -> audit.conf and
# edit — but do not commit the result. It contains your namespace,
# user names, cluster-specific paths, and is unique per deployment.
/audit.conf

# Collector output. These directories contain raw logs, error
# samples, and record-level JSON from your pipeline — which very
# likely includes PHI/PII/PII-adjacent data. Never commit them.
/capsule-audit-latest/
/*-audit-latest/
/*-audit-*/
*-capsule-audit-*/

# Generated summary (written alongside artifacts by -m / -o)
SUMMARY.md

# Local-only audit prompt (internal tool, not part of the public repo)
/AUDIT_PROMPT.md

# Editor / OS junk
*~
*.swp
*.swo
*.bak
*.orig
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Shell history if someone cd's here
.bash_history
